import React, { useState } from 'react'; import axios from 'axios'; import { LineChart, Line, XAxis, YAxis, CartesianGrid, Tooltip, Legend, ResponsiveContainer } from 'recharts'; function App() { // State for PDF upload const [file, setFile] = useState(null); // State to store the parsed transactions from the server const [transactions, setTransactions] = useState([]); // Sample data for the "Analytics" charts const monthlyIncomeData = [ { month: 'Jan', amount: 3000 }, { month: 'Feb', amount: 3500 }, { month: 'Mar', amount: 4000 }, { month: 'Apr', amount: 4500 }, { month: 'May', amount: 4200 }, { month: 'Jun', amount: 4600 } ]; const monthlyExpenseData = [ { month: 'Jan', amount: 2000 }, { month: 'Feb', amount: 1800 }, { month: 'Mar', amount: 2100 }, { month: 'Apr', amount: 2200 }, { month: 'May', amount: 2300 }, { month: 'Jun', amount: 2500 } ]; const handleFileChange = (e) => { setFile(e.target.files[0]); }; const handleUpload = async () => { if (!file) return; try { const formData = new FormData(); formData.append('file', file); // This expects your POST /upload-pdf endpoint const res = await axios.post('http://localhost:8000/upload-pdf', formData, { headers: { 'Content-Type': 'multipart/form-data' }, }); console.log('Server response:', res.data); // Assuming the server returns { "status": "success", "transactions": [...] } if (res.data.transactions) { setTransactions(res.data.transactions); } alert('PDF uploaded and parsed successfully!'); } catch (error) { console.error(error); alert('Error uploading file.'); } }; return (
